<p>Trace, I watched this series on the plane and found it very entertaining when they explored the Medici family and the usury laws but then when they showed the Rothschild interview and the Bond markets it just felt like it was missing a lot of key elements, some of which you mentioned, which they skirted around and ignored. I was wondering if the book would be worth reading to see if they went more in depth but now I know it was just like the series. I do like how there are more programs about money being created.</p>
