<div class="format_text" id="comment-body-19095">
<p>Interestingly Mr. Ferguson has written a book on the House of Rothschild. I do not necessarily think there is a huge market for a book on the Rothschild&#8217;s which begs the question: how is this book going to be profitable and who is paying for it? Additionally, his general tenor seems like he is an apologist &#8230; almost like he has been hired by their PR firm or something which would go towards answering those questions. Lots of skirting and lots of ignoring.</p>
